social_posts.post_text: Agree? Disagree?

Enrollment for May is open! I still have a few spots.

Don’t wait another month. There is still time to make 2023 your best year yet. Start today.

Here are some of the most outstanding people I’ve had the privilege of helping. (The last one is/was Fatboi Mark.)

"I'm like 3% body fat."

Dude... No you're not. 

If you were 3% body fat you would be in the hospital (or dead).

The best, most genetically gifted bodybuilders MIGHT approach that low of a body fat level for a day (more likely only a few hours).

You are not sustainably walking around daily ANYWHERE NEAR THAT.

Unless you have Bo Jackson genetics, and/or are on a load of drugs, you're probably not maintaining even single digit body fat levels year-round without a good bit of suffering. 

(And if that's what you want to attempt, you can forget about gaining any appreciable amount of muscle.)

And NO, you cannot step on an electronic scale with some handles and get anywhere near accurate readings of your body fat. Unfortunately. 

Bodpod and DEXA scan are relatively accurate (yet STILL have a margin for error).

Pretty much anything else has such a huge margin for error that it's useless—don't even bother.

It's only going to mindfuck you, one way or the other.

It's just a number, anyway.

You either like the way you look in the mirror or you don't.

Maybe you know you need to drop some fat to get the look you want, or maybe the current goal is to gain muscle...

Is a number on a piece of paper or screen going to change that how you feel about that?

ALSO: I’ve included the best examples/reference points I could find, from a couple of @menno.henselmans articles. Both men and women. Swipe to check them out.

🚨 SCAM ALERT 🚨

I’ve tagged some of the top-appearing 'cleanse' and 'detox' accounts to give you some examples of BS to stay away from.

If you want a simple and easy way to enhance your health and your life in general, go for walks. 

This is created on the back of @gregnuckols and @strongerbyscience review of the meta analysis mentioned (PMID : 34417979). 

We found the findings about the differences between smoking and high BMI versus not walking enough on all cause mortality quite striking and certainly worth a mention, don’t go smoking more and gain a tonne of fat just because, obviously 😂 

If you can clear more time to walk if you don’t walk a lot, you will most likely score a decent amount of health and longevity points.
